Getting started

getting-started.Rmd
library(MASS)

X <-  longley[,-7]
y <- longley[, 7]
fit_obj <- matern32::fit_matern32(x = X, y = y)
## Registered S3 method overwritten by 'matern32':
##   method       from 
##   predict.poly stats
par(mfrow=c(1, 2))
 
plot(log(fit_obj$lambda), fit_obj$GCV, type = 'l', main = "GCV", 
ylab = "GCV")

matplot(log(fit_obj$lambda), t(fit_obj$coef), type = 'l', 
main = "coefficients = f(lambda)", xlab = "log(lambda)", 
ylab = "coefs")
abline(h = 0, lty = 2, lwd = 2, col = "red")

summary_fit_obj <- summary(fit_obj)

X <- as.matrix(Boston[,-14])
y <- Boston[,14]

set.seed(123)
idx_train <- sample.int(dim(X)[1], size=floor(0.8*dim(X)[1]))
fit_obj <- matern32::fit_matern32(x = X[idx_train,], y = y[idx_train], lambda = 0.01)

summary_fit_obj <- summary(fit_obj)
